x4freetext: The Lawrence Berkeley Laboratory 88-
inch cyclotron.
The 248Cm and 249Cf targets were
irradiated at the Lawrence Berkeley Laboratory
88-inch cyclotron with 97-, 104-, 113-, and 122-MeV
180 ions. In addition, the 249Cf was irradiated with
91- and 150- MeV 18O ions.
All quoted energies have been corrected for the total
energy loss of about 15 MeV in the Havar window,
cooling gas, and Be target backing. No corrections
were made for the energy losses of 1 to 2 MeV in the
targets.

x4freetext: Similar to EXFOR entry A0173: The target contained
the form Cm-F/3 deposited with a diam. of 6.5 mm on
2.65 mg/cm2 `Be` foil.
Gold foils, 19.5 mm in diam. and 2 mg/cm2 thick, were
placed 3 mm from the target to catch the recoiling
products.
No absolute gamma-ray intensity data are
available for the 0.177-MeV photon which we measured,
but the 0.177-MeV level in 251Cf is deexcited by a
0.177-MeV gamma transition (72.5%) and a 0.153-MeV
gamma transition (27.5%) . The total conversion
coefficient for the 0.177 gamma transition was
estimated to be =8 based on a measured alphaK of 6.0
and an estimated (alphaL+alphaM) of 1.7 for an M1(+
E2) transition. The decay of 251Bk is assumed to
primarily populate the 0.177- MeV level. If there is
appreciable feeding of the ground state or other
levels which do not deexcite via the 0.177-MeV
transition, our quoted cross sections will be
correspondingly too 1ow.
